<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code calls daemon->unescape_callback(c->daemon->unescape_callback_cls, c, c->rq.hdrs.rq_line.rq_tgt) passing only a char* (no length). If the callback internally uses string.h routines (strlen/strcpy/memcpy/etc.) it will rely on proper NUL-termination of rq_tgt. The function's NUL-termination is only established by logic that writes a '\0' when a '?' is present and by debug-time asserts (strlen(...) == computed length). Those asserts may be compiled out and there is no unconditional guarantee in this snippet that rq_tgt is NUL-terminated in all builds/paths. Thus the call can lead to string.h functions accessing beyond the bounds of the object referenced by rq_tgt (out-of-bounds reads/writes) and violates Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
